-- Honda posts adjusted 1 pct. gain in U.S. February sales
-- 
-- Mon Mar 3, 2008 2:24pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/03/us-usa-autosales-honda-idUSWNAS333120080303

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Honda Motor Co ( 7267.T ) on Monday posted an increase of just under 1 percent in U.S. vehicle sales in February after adjusting for the number of selling days in the month compared with a year earlier. 

 The automaker said it had sold 115,397 vehicles in the U.S. market in February compared with 110,026 a year earlier. Honda's reported 0.7 percent gain in monthly sales was adjusted for one additional sales day in February compared with a year earlier.